text: - My name is Cynthia Davis,

and I'm a manager of an incredible
partner development team

supporting North America
consulting partners.

I joined AWS because I
wanted to work for a company
that was making history.
I come from a telco space,

and it was really exciting
to work in telecommunications
back in the early 2000s.

And I was looking for
that opportunity again,

and the pace of innovation
at AWS is really exciting.
(upbeat music)

The most surprising
thing or highlight for me

in the last five years
is being able to build
and enable a new partner development team
supporting strategic partners.
I started, I was part of a team of six,
and now I'm part of a team of 30.

And so I get the opportunity
to build up my own team

and start from ground zero
to bring new partners in
is such an incredible opportunity.
(upbeat music)

There are a number of groups
that I'm involved with
outside of AWS.
The one that comes top of mind

is a group called Leading
Women in Technology.
I'm a member of that group,

and I'm passionate about helping
other women get into tech.
The culture at AWS is really unique,
and it was something I thought I knew,
until I joined the organization,

and then realized this
moves at a faster pace
than I've ever been used to before.

And so being really
comfortable with prioritizing

and getting comfortable
with the uncomfortable

is something I would
have people think about
before joining the organization,

'cause it's really exciting
and you wanna take it all on.
But you have to sometimes pump the brakes,
'cause there's a lot of innovation.
(upbeat music)
